            "summary": "During midday trading on Friday, all three major indices were in the red, with the S&P 500 and Nasdaq 100 experiencing declines of 1% and 1.24%, respectively. These drops put them on track for their worst weeks since September 2024. The Nasdaq entered correction territory on Friday after plummeting over 10% below its peak in February. Market turmoil was largely attributed to tariff announcements and uncertainty throughout the week. President Donald Trump made headlines on Thursday by halting all tariffs on products governed by the North American trade agreement until April 2, but this had minimal impact on market volatility. The stock market has been highly reactive to tariff news, leading to heightened levels of volatility.",
